    <section id="introduction" aria-labelledby="intro-heading">
      <h2 id="intro-heading">Introduction</h2>
      <p>This page demonstrates the use of semantic HTML5 elements along with accessibility features and SEO techniques. The goal is to build a well-structured web page that is both user- and machine-friendly.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="accessibility" aria-labelledby="access-heading">
      <h2 id="access-heading">Web Accessibility</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>Why Accessibility Matters</h3>
        <p>Accessibility ensures that all users, including those with disabilities, can access and navigate websites effectively. Semantic HTML and proper use of ARIA attributes improve support for screen readers and other assistive technologies.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Best Practices</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use meaningful landmarks like <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>.</li>
          <li>Label form fields with <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> and use <code>aria-label</code> where necessary.</li>
          <li>Ensure content is readable and navigable with keyboard input.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="seo" aria-labelledby="seo-heading">
      <h2 id="seo-heading">Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>SEO Fundamentals</h3>
        <p>SEO involves making your website content discoverable and indexable by search engines. Semantic tags and meaningful metadata play a critical role.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>On-Page SEO Tips</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use heading tags in proper order (<code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>).</li>
          <li>Include descriptive <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;meta&gt;</code> tags.</li>
          <li>Write clear, keyword-rich, human-friendly content.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
      <h2 id="contact-heading">Contact</h2>
      <form action="/submit" method="post" aria-label="Contact Form">
